        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Promo-image-for-Stranger-Than-Heaven-showing-a-male-with-very-blue-eyes-smoking.-An-Xbox-logo-is-in-the-upper-left-hand-corner.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>Eurogamer</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>Microsoft has announced its next Xbox Partner Preview showcase will take place later this week, and focus on third-party games from the likes of Sega and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/companies/gsc-game-world">GSC Game World</a>.</p>
<p>The stream will take place on Thursday, 26th March, kicking off at 5pm UK time. That's 10am Pacific / 1pm Eastern for those across the pond. It will all last for roughly 30 minutes. </p>
<!-- code from Primis - Eurogamer.net - eurogamer.net -->
<div>
<p><span data-type="targeting">
<span>To see this content please enable targeting cookies.</span>
</span> </p>
</div>
<!-- code from Primis -->
<p>As for which games we can expect to see, Microsoft has promised more on Ryu Ga Gotoku's newest project known as Stranger Than Heaven, as well as an update on <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/stalker-2-heart-of-chornobyl-review">Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl</a> and new looks at The Expanse: Osiris Reborn.</p>
<p>There will also be some other bits and pieces to look forward to, with Microsoft promising brand-new reveals and world premieres along with more information about games coming to Game Pass. You will be able to watch this week's Xbox Partner Preview showcase via <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/xbox">YouTube</a> and <a href="https://www.twitch.tv/Xbox">Twitch</a>.</p>

<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="STRANGER THAN HEAVEN - Announcement Teaser Trailer" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Dz3vtzcacbM?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>STRANGER THAN HEAVEN - Announcement Teaser Trailer</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Dz3vtzcacbM?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/Dz3vtzcacbM?autoplay=1" title="STRANGER THAN HEAVEN - Announcement Teaser Trailer">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>Stranger Than Heaven - Announcement Teaser Trailer.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dz3vtzcacbM" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>


<p>I will admit, I had forgotten about Stranger Than Heaven, so it will be good to see what Ryu Ga Gotoku has been working on since that initial reveal back 2024, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/sega-unveils-new-virtua-fighter-sonic-racing-and-like-a-dragon">when it was known as the Project Century</a>. It's a <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/yakuza-studios-project-century-gets-a-proper-name-and-a-stylish-new-trailer">third-person action game with real-time combat set in an open city</a>, this one whisking players back to 1915. You can check out a trailer for Stranger Than Heaven in the video above.</p>
<p>We here at Eurogamer will of course be watching along on Thursday, so be sure to join us for all the chat and news as it happens. Bring snacks!</p>

